messages.message: @lydia I’m not familiar with “the new ib_llm_tools package” where can I find some context on that?

@Sławek Biel - the new ib_llm_tools package is a devex package that can be used to call LLMs through refiner. The package provides the user two functions (1) `call_model_build` to use aihub build capabilites and (2) `call_model_converse` to use aihub converse capabilities. This package should replace the script that sales eng is using beginning in 23.07 as environments (including sandboxes) will be deployed with aihub backend services.

The package is available for testing on dogfood right now (with minor improvements being made before widely announced). The package can be accessed directly through refiner by installing the package into your refiner from the marketplace icon. Version 0.0.1-dev12 of the package is the latest.
Let me know if you need any more context
Where can I find the source? The marketplace package seems encrypted
Adding in @pauline.comising @Kathy Wu who might be able to share with you
ah ya, you can find the code in the appengrepo repo (https://github.com/instabase/appengrepo/blob/master/packages/ib_aihubhelper/src/ai_hub.py)
